Subject: ナビはイマイチ
Body:
地図としての機能はとても良いと思います。
正確かつ操作も直感的です。
ただ、ナビとして見ると、どうも最短距離を選択する志向が強くて、無意味に細い道を走らされるケースが多いように思います。
この辺りはYahoo!ナビの方が、ルート候補を選べたりして、高い評価をつけてます。
それでも、市街地に入ったらルートを確認しながら、ショートカットをさせようと思ってるなと思えば、指示に従わないことで回避できます。
Translated Body: I think the function as a map is very good. It is accurate and operation intuitive. However, as a navigator, it seems that there are many cases in which it is strongly oriented to select the shortest distance, and it runs a narrow road meaninglessly. In this area, Yahoo! Navi is better able to choose candidate routes, and has a high rating. Still, if you go into an urban area and think that you are going to do a shortcut while checking the route, you can avoid it by not obeying instructions.

Author: realdriftwood
Subject: Really exceptionally dependable routing
Body: I have been using GPS in my vehicles since 2007, so I have dealt with a number of different systems for over ten years now, and I have spent lot of money on navigation systems installed in vehicles (eight different vehicles over that period). I still use a built-in system in my present vehicle. But increasingly—and since iPhone 5 and iPhone 6—I have been depending on Google Maps to route me to specific destinations, and using my car’s BlueTooth connection system to provide continuous directions through my car’s sound system. I have found it extremely reliable, and I certainly have appreciated that it is constantly updated and free. As most newer cars can connect with their owners’ smartphones now—and as most smartphones can be charged in the car—I highly recommend this application to everyone who has to do a lot of driving!

Author: Yadira1738
Subject: I was in love.
Body:
I fell in love with Google Maps maybe about 7 years ago. It’s the reason I was one of the quickest pizza delivery drivers and why I’m always the one navigating family trips. I’ve been in Europe for 3 months now, and I rely desperately on my saved locations when exploring new countries. It was working beautifully until about 2 weeks ago (I assume with this new update), and when I was in London last week I was struggling to hit all the places I planned on because the map was refusing to show my saved places (my data is slow so I rely on Google Maps). I’m taking my last trip tomorrow and I don’t want to say that Google Maps is going to ruin the trip - but it definitely won’t make my trip any easier (like it used to). 

This is coming from a Google Maps enthusiast that annoys all her friends when she worships it (and bashes all other “Maps”). Please Google, fix this problem. I’m sure you won’t be able to for my trip tomorrow, but if my comment helps someone else, then AWESOME! And to the Google Team, I love you. Really. Thank you. May you get all the donuts you deserve.

Author: Andy.2d02
Subject: Life changer
Body:
I have been using Google maps for past 7 years however I never got time to credit the usage. Over this time I have seen the way the application has been changing by taking all the feedbacks very seriously.
I have used primarily for my road trips and it had been life changing experience where we typically end up along lot of people for directions and now this app has totally changes it by showing the shortest possible path to the most remote location possible.
Though sometime my privacy gets breached but the advantage I get is dobson I can surely trade off.
In the end would just like to say thank you Google for giving an app that changes the way people travel.

Author: ivaluefreedom
Subject: GIVE UP LOTS OF PERSONAL INFO FOF A SMALL BIT OF CONVENIENCE
Body: I only purchased this app to test my new security features, after which I reset my device. As an American citizen, it’s amazing how passive this nation has become. I am saddened by how willing the majority of Americans no longer value things like privacy and freedom of speech and have no aversion giving up their personal information to a corporation that makes an immense profit capitalizing on it. I remind the American people that even law abiding citizens should value privacy. There is a huge misconception that only criminals should be worried about their privacy. Wrong! Well, I warn you all, you all keep this erosion going, in ten years, the US Constitution will exist only to a small group of people employed at Alphabet Inc. (Google’s holding company) for they will be the only people who know that such a document was even written. So long as the US allows Google, Apple and Microsoft to merge, which will eventually happen (I’d give it 7 years), one extremely profitable and unregulated corporation will hold the key to 100% of all information online and by default, control every government in the world. The worse part about it is only only a small minority of Americans will be able to say, “we did not support it.” And good news for you all who just keep  handing Alphabet Inc. your personal information in exchange for a tiny bit of convenience, soon you all won’t even have to read any service agreement or even think about anything. That’s because Alphabet Inc. will do all that for you. Why do you think Google chose that name?

Author: massa03
Subject: iPhone Xでは使いづらい→改善されました
Body:
アプリがXに対応したところ、ナビ画面で一気に使いづらくなりました。ホーム画面に戻れないという。これはかなり酷いです。

具体的にはホームに戻るジェスチャーと下に隠れたタブを引っ張り上げるジェスチャーが同じで、アプリ側のジェスチャーが優先されます。

よってホームに戻る前に数回ほど上にスライドする必要があります。しかも必ずうまくいくわけでもなく時にはホーム画面に戻れないことも。その場合はナビを一旦終了しなければなりません。

見直していただきUIの改善を願っています。

—————
再レビュー 20171231

上記の指摘が即改善されたようです。
開発者の方ありがとうございます！
さすがですね。

あとは車の大きさと実際の道幅を考慮したナビが出来るようになれば、それこそ無双のナビアプリになると思うので、将来的にそんな仕様もご検討ください。

絶対に車は通れないでしょ、って細い道を問答無用でゴリ推ししてくるのが皆が悩んでいる最大の問題なので是非解決してください。
Translated Subject: It was hard to use on iPhone X → It was improved
Translated Body: When the application corresponds to X, it became difficult to use at once with the navigation screen. It is said that it can not return to the home screen. This is pretty terrible. Specifically, the gesture that returns to the home and the gesture that pulls up the hidden tab are the same, and the gesture of the application side takes precedence. So before you return to home you need to slide upwards several times. Besides, it does not necessarily go well, and sometimes I can not go back to the home screen. In that case you have to quit Navi. We hope to improve and improve UI. ----- Re-review 20171231 The above indication seems to have been improved immediately. Thanks to the developers! That's right. After that I think that it will be a musou car navigation application if it becomes possible to navigate considering the size of the car and the actual road width so please consider such specifications in the future. 86版《西游记》关于女儿国的一集里，有这样一个片段：

深夜，唐僧与女儿国国王在闺房中谈话。身姿曼妙、美若天仙的女儿国国王，对唐僧心生爱慕，于是提出要与他共享双宿双飞的万千之喜。

面对这求欢之意的唐僧，显得手足无措，随即闭上双眼掩饰道：“佛心四大皆空，贫僧尘念已绝，无缘消受人间富贵。”

女儿国国王嫣然一笑：“你说四大皆空，却紧闭双眼，要是你睁开眼睛看看我，我不相信你两眼空空。”

听了这话的唐僧愈加慌乱、头冒冷汗，连念数声“阿弥陀佛”以定心性。

女儿国国王见状，更是对唐僧屡屡相逼。在来来回回的拉扯与推搡之后，唐僧终于站定身子，背对佳人叹道：

“女王陛下，贫僧已许身佛门，并与大唐天子有诺在先，还望女王陛下放贫僧西去。”

女儿国国王闻言，神情一黯，转身挪步几尺。而唐僧迟疑片刻，回眸柔声道：“来世若有缘分……”

哪怕堂堂圣僧，哪怕心怀戒律清规，哪怕坚称四大皆空，却还是逃不开那种由深处绽放出的怦然心动，甚至不惜破戒、说出深情的话语。

Body: There is numerous times where google map not showing exact location of me others. It’s sometimes irritating when you need to reach your distance timely but map doesn’t work properly. Plz rectify or stop giving ads for google maps.

Author: BBrandml
Subject: Nicht mehr zuverlässig und bugfrei
Body: Viele Jahre war Google Maps meine unschlagbare Nummer 1 der Karten/Navi Apps. Tatsächlich muss ich mich jetzt nach Alternativen umschauen. Die Navigation funktioniert nicht mehr zuverlässig und lang bekannte Straßensperren werden nicht erkannt. Zudem habe ich nun seit mehreren Wochen einen inakzeptablen Bug: POIs werden auf der Karte zwar angezeigt, aber die App stürzt ab wenn ich hoch swipe um die Details zu sehen! —> unbenutzbar. Ist stets reproduzierbar und betrifft alle POIs
Translated Subject: No longer reliable and bug free
Translated Body: For many years, Google Maps has been my unbeatable # 1 map / sat nav apps. In fact, I have to look for alternatives now. Navigation is no longer reliable and long-known roadblocks are not detected. In addition, I have now for several weeks an unacceptable bug: POIs are displayed on the map, but the app crashes when I swipe up to see the details! -> unusable. Is always reproducible and affects all POIs

Author: Alexey1502
Subject: Прекрасные карты, но ужасный навигатор
Body:
Давно пользуюсь картами и очень очень разочарован работой навигатора. 
Построение маршрута можно назвать просто странным, но сам навигатор просто ужас! Любая развязка сложнее обычной бабочки ставит его в тупик, из-за чего выбор полосы не работает никогда! Единственный вариант - пользоваться указателям (если они есть).
Уважаемые разработчики, доработайте программу пожалуйста!
Translated Subject: Beautiful maps, but a terrible navigator
Translated Body: I have been using maps for a long time and I am very disappointed with the work of the navigator. The construction of the route can be called simply strange, but the navigator itself is simply horrible! Any denouement is more complicated than an ordinary butterfly puts it in a dead end, because of what the choice of the strip does not work ever! The only option is to use pointers (if any). Dear developers, modify the program please!

Author: Serenityx1234029483828
Subject: Review from UPS driver
Body:
Considering the amount of resources a company like google has, its truly shocking at how primitive Google maps is considering what other apps have to offer. Route optimization for multiple routes should have been a thing atleast 4 years ago. Anytime Ive got more than 7-8 addresses queued for delivery and try re-organizing them to optimize the path it bugs out and doesn’t change the order, making things confusing as hell and forcing me to re-start the app to clear the bug and spend another 5 minutes re-typing half a dozen addresses. Considering I have to deliver up to and over 180-200 places a day (mostly residential homes, but some routes have more businesses than homes and vice versa) 5-10 minutes of inputting and optimizing routes every 7-8 stops Ive done the math and its a disgusting amount of time wasted with this app. 

Its unfortunate there are to my knowledge 0 functional/working iOS apps that offer things like SIMPLE ROUTE OPTIMIZATION. Its a shame google has not put more consideration into this product with delivery drivers in mind. Id easily pay a hefty subscription for access to an iOS program that has more features with delivery drivers in mind. I’ll suggest 30$ a month for what an app like In Route does but that actually functions.

Here’s what Id pay that obscene price for:

1. Route optimization for atleast 5-10 stops within a certain distance radius. Im not expecting to be able to put 20-30 stops in that span over a few quarter miles and have it optimized Im talking maybe stops within the size of 2 neighborhoods. All I need is to be able to optimize my path through one neighborhood and to the next (e.g. if I have 8 streets to deliver to in one neighborhood, I need to be able to optimize atleast 9 stops. Thats optimization for the 8 streets in the first neighborhood that ends with a path to my next neighborhood where I can repeat the process and have 8 more stops optimized the last which would simply direct me to my next area.)

2. An improved search feature!! If the last 200 places Ive been (no exaggeration here) are in the same city and within 1 mile of eachother, what are the chances my next location is going to be in another bloody state? How hard is it to prioritize/limit search results based on proximity here???? 
In short, the ability to filter searches  so I dont have to wade through the dozens of streets with similar names in other cities/states. 
Optimizing search results based on proximity to previous searches would just be a cherry on top here. 

3. Thats mostly everything I can think of off the top of my head, Im mostly willing to pay a small subscription for primitive route optimization feature, the more complex that feature becomes the more Im willing to pay monthly. I sincerely hope google considers this review. Please let me know why this cant be done.

On peut même s’interroger sur la capacité du développeur à savoir réagir vite sur son app.
C’est vraiment dommage mais j’ai donc supprimé cette app. Je ferai une nouvelle notation lorsqu’elle sera mise à jour.

Author: JLAuBuchon
Subject: So close, yet so far
Body:
I’d like to see full screen use on the iPhone X like Google Maps or even something similar to Apple Maps. It’s trivial I’m sure, but it’s attention to detail. It does appear night mode uses true black which will conserve battery. Being able to download maps is great, it saved us on our last trip to Europe and made getting around a breeze. I also haven’t noticed any ads lately, which was fairly annoying not to be able to opt out of. It would be nice to have an auto switch feature for the units, it’s already using our location, can’t be that hard to know what areas use which units on their roads, there are only three. The voices are a bit digital and processed sounding, not major, but smoother voices would be nice. The directions can be confusing, especially the lane indicators and arrows. If you’re a Windows 10 user you’ll notice the native MS Maps app is in fact Here We Go. This made planning trips in Europe easier since we could see things on my Surface Pro 4 in larger detail then use the iPhone on the streets for navigation.

Reality is I’d only use Google Maps if they offered offline maps. However, they don’t, so this is where Here We Go really shines. If Here We Go could get their interface, search and options on par with Google Maps, I may just remove Google Maps. At the moment there’s a long ways to go still.

Body: Nie mogę zaktualizować dochodzi do 75 procent i wywala błąd a było tak dobrze :-(
Vec sam poslao svoje misljenje tvorcu aplikacije .

Byla to dobrá navigace. Škoda že už se nedá nastavit jestli chci rychlou, vyváženou nebo ekonomickou trasu. Navigace vede tak, aby ušetřila pár Km a tahá po nejhorších silnicích, kde je to tak na zničení podvozku. Kolikrát chce jet i do ulice se zakázaným průjezdem. Někdy jsou ty zkratky na zabití, když se táhnete půl hodiny do kopce po té nejhorší kostkovici, kde se dá stěží vyhnout autu, Tatra by to mohla úspěšně použít jako polygon, lidi musí uhýbat a diví se kde se tu ten pitomec vzal,  po příjezdu pak zjistíte, že na místo vede hezká asfatka jen o kilometr delší. Po aktualizaci už se ani nespustí.

Author: PIYUSH TRIPATHI
Body: (P.S.- First of all this is a detailed review, so if you clicked here to just glance at rating, continue scrolling.) The use which an average person puts through his/her map application is to chalk out routes to places they are unfamiliar of. This is one of those apps which will allow you to do the same without hassles, unlike others. The features include allowing us to chart routes keeping in mind the road traffic, set up waystations or stops in our route and essentially helps us manage time efficiently. This is a boon for someone like me whose hobby is travelling to unknown localities and places. Also marking out the important landmarks is a great way to plan routes and this has also been adequately addressed. Included is a fantastic guide program with great perks. All in all this is one of those apps where Google did everything right. Keep up the good works.

А стоит его отключить, так оно само себя включает через пару дней и опять скачивает хрень всякую. Самое обидное, что его нельзя удалить с телефона.
Translated Body: A strange idea for such a large company. From year to year, it only gets worse. Now he always downloads offline maps of all places I've visited, although I do not even use this poor application. Ogni volta che disattivo queste opzioni dalle impostazioni posso stare tranquillo una settimana al massimo, poi magicamente tutto torna attivato e vengo tempestato di notifiche sul traffico che non mi interessano e il telefono mi si riempie di mappe offline che non ho richiesto. Risolvete.
Translated Body: In my opinion it is not about the maps that for me are appreciable and the guide items for me work well, but rather the unbearable inability to get rid of the notifications and offline maps automatic. Every time I disable these options from the settings I can feel comfortable for a week at most, then magically everything goes back on and I get traffic notifications that do not interest me and the phone fills me with offline maps that I have not requested. Solve.

Body: Non mi piace il modo in cui si utilizza lo Street View, sono sicuro di non essere l'unico a non apprezzarlo. Il problema sta nello spostamento tramite le linee guida che è troppo sensibile, a ciò si aggiunge anche lo spostamento della visuale (che è fondamentale per lo Street View) che confonde i due comandi (spostamento sulla strada e movimento di visuale). Io spero che con un futuro aggiornamento si possa eliminare questo comando di spostare trascinandosi la linea con delle frecce possibilmente in qualche angolo dello schermo.

Поехал из Новороссийска в Ростов-на-Дону, точнее по области. Как человек вообще не знающий местности, я полностью доверился этому ....навигатору.  Мало того что эта сволочь меня водила кругами по городам (вокруг одной и той же точки на карте) ,думал может какой сбой, НО!!! Дальше было ещё лучше- приводила меня постоянно к тупикам,утверждая что там есть дорого и можно проехать-по факту там были ж-д пути,которые можно было бы форсировать еслиб я был на УАЗике. И так неоднократно, а другой путь просто не отображался.  И САМОЕ ЧТО ПРИВЕЛО МЕНЯ ПРОСТО А БЕШЕНСТВО--- предложила проехать от одного до другого нас.пункта (буквально 10км). Я поехал ииии ВУАЛЯ СКА- передо мной поле!!! Навигация говорит-поехали! .... Дамы и господа для полной картины - погодные условия -туман,чуток моросит дождик,температура за бортом +12 время 2й час ночи и полевая дорога!!!!! У меня ГАЗЕЛЬ!!!ГАЗЕЛЬ СКА , не УАЗ на грязевой резине... Во общем Гугл дрянь! Я поседел и нервы сдали нахрен. Фу

Body: Es una App amigable, fácil, actual.  Yo la uso con mucha regularidad y tengo un par de sugerencias para futuras actualizaciones: 1)Que Las búsquedas sean prioritarias según el lugar en el que te encuentres,(me pasa que quiero buscar un lugar cercano y me manda  hasta la otra punta del planeta solo porque el nombre es el mismo y tengo que especificar mucho para que me de la dirección que estoy buscando)  2)Poder guardar mas fácil un trayecto y tenerlo a la mano en el menú lateral  3) creo que esta es la que mas me interesa, el transporte publico de mi zona no me aparece me gustaría que se enfocarán también en esa haria; que no la descuiden ya que han decidido añadirla. Eso es todo y muchas gracias, de hay en fuera ¡muy bien!
Translated Body: It is a friendly, easy, current App. I use it very regularly and I have a couple of suggestions for future updates: 1) That the searches are priority according to the place where you are, (it happens to me that I want to look for a place nearby and send me to the other side of the planet just because the name is the same and I have to specify a lot to give me the address I'm looking for) 2) To be able to save a trip easier and have it on hand in the side menu 3) I think this is the one that interests me the most , the public transport of my zone does not appear to me I would like that they will also focus on that task; Do not neglect it because you have decided to add it. That's it and thank you very much, there's a very good outside!

Body: Está bastante bien pero el modo de navegación debe mejorar mucho en lo que respecta a las instrucciones por voz ya que no son claras muchas de ellas como por ejemplo la que indica que tome en una determinada dirección (por ejemplo suroeste) hacia una determinada calle de nombre tal (por ejemplo "tome la avenida Andalucía en dirección noreste"). Un usuario que no conozca la ciudad por la que se mueve no conoce ni mucho menos los nombres de las calles y tendría dificultades para saber la orientación. Es por ello que este tipo de instrucciones no ayudan y es estrictamente necesario mirar el mapa en la pantalla para ver por dónde te está indicando que debes coger.
Translated Body: It is quite good but the navigation mode should improve a lot with respect to the voice instructions since many of them are not clear, such as the one that indicates that it takes a certain direction (for example southwest) towards a certain street of such name (for example "take Andalusia Avenue in northeastern direction"). A user who does not know the city he is moving around does not know much about the names of the streets and would have difficulty knowing the orientation. That is why this type of instruction does not help and it is strictly necessary to look at the map on the screen to see where it is indicating you should take it.

Body: Pior atualização do mundo. Era meu GPS preferido, usei literalmente em quase todo mundo. Porém deppis desta última atualização ficou pessimo. A orientação de todas gelada nao funciona mais. O indicador nao aparece mais como um.icone somente a bolinha azul. Não recalcula automaticamente a rota. Não mostra mais o tempo e a distância para o destino final e não é possível reconfigurar como era antes. Em resumo, estou no meio de uma viagem e fiquei completamente sem orientação porque confiava no Google Maps e agora ficou pessimo. Pior atualização que já vi, ao invés de aprimorar retrocederam, seria como voltar ao DOS.
Translated Body: Worst update in the world. It was my favorite GPS, I used it literally in almost everyone. But deppis of this last update was awful. The orientation of all ice cream does not work anymore. The indicator does not appear more like a.icone only the blue ball. Does not recalculate the route automatically. It no longer shows the time and distance to the final destination and can not be reconfigured as it was before. In summary, I'm in the middle of a trip and I was completely without guidance because I trusted Google Maps and now it's terrible. Worst update I have ever seen, instead of hardening back, would be like back to DOS.

Body: This app will not follow preplanned routes. It changes routes you choose mid-trip without telling you. Have driven across the country and have to constantly re-route Google maps back to my planned route. And the fastest route suggestions are not the fastest route. In one instance, it suggested county road with stop lights instead of the highway and there was no accident/construction that would warrant a re-route. And when i want to take back roads, it reroutes to the highway! I literally use it to zoom in and out on map to find my own route and then I ignore it. If you are a mindless driver who doesn't care how you get to where you are going or sitting at lights, this app will work for you.

Author: Robbie Pike
Body: I've been using this App for over a year and have waited to write this review.  Pros: Alerts Speed Traps Cons: Does not give the fastest route GPS never knows where I'm at Many times this App has caused me take a longer way Traffic updates are way too slow Whatever that ticker things is not accurate at all, I'll be in traffic and it and it always shows that I'm not there yet, no clue why it functions that way. Way too many buttons to get simple directions.  I'd pay for this App if it worked better with finding faster routes and GPS lag. I drove the same route through town because it's faster than sitting in traffic, this App would keep telling me to get back on the freeway so I could sit. My route was 10 mins faster but this App would never tell me to go that way. Google Maps would tell to take the route I used to skip traffic.

Body: Um dia já foi bom! Nós últimos meses vem calculando o tempo de viagem errado, muito a mais do real ou abaixo e aí vai adicionando mais minutos,  ou seja, nunca sei quanto vou demorar realmente. Além disso esta fazendo comparativo de rotas sem nexo, exemplo: informa que o caminho selecionado é 50 minutos mais rápido que a segunda opção, a segunda opção é um caminho absurdo sem noção!  O pior é se mudou de direção o Waze não percebe se não reiniciar. O Google Maps é muito superior, só uso o Waze porque informa onde estão os radares!

App: Waze - GPS, Maps, Traffic Alerts & Live Navigation
Author: En av Googles användare
Body: As a commuter tool it was and still is promising. However, typing this as we're stuck in a jam that Waze got us into, rather than out of. This happen from time. But it does have made situational awareness in traffic and common and useful thing. No doubt.   As a mapping and navigation tool it us rather poor. It dies gives the next instruction too late while driving. It lags even on high end devices when driving in traffic in city with many streets and turns. Almost always when starting a drive it totally lack orientation and is useless until you have drive a while.  Other quite annoying shortcomings include total failure to work while driving in tunnels (why on earth not extrapolate speed and direction and adjust with speed limit?) and speed camera warnings and other pop-ups obscuring relevant parts of map (what's ahead...)  At the end of the day this is still my preferred choice of navigation app. It is a Swiss army knife, can do many things, comes in handy but is rather limited in how good it does things.

It couldn't tell me where I was because I didn't have any WiFi, just because I remembered the street I was looking for, it guided me all the way there so thank you Great navigation also. App Name: Waze - GPS, Maps, Traffic Alerts & Live Navigation
App: Waze - GPS, Maps, Traffic Alerts & Live Navigation
Author: Mike Boyd
Body: Waze has some good things and some bad. The good things are: * It let's you know where the cops are * It can beep if you go over the speed limit (configurable) * It lets you know when there's junk in the road * It lets you know where accidents are  Some of the bad things are: * It crashes at least once every 4 hours usually very quietly and at the WORST POSSIBLE TIME.  We take a 10 hour trip up the coast, and I use waze for all the positives mentioned above, but it always crashes at least twice and my wife says "Ugh, why do you even use that app". Seriously people, stability is a HUGE thing if you're on a long trip and relying on waze to tell you the next turn * The "let me figure out where you're going next" feature is a real pain in the rear.  At most it should ask if you're going somewhere, if you don't respond, it should *not* automatically tell you how to get there.  Especially if you're going home from work. I know how to get home! I don't want the darn thing to interrupt my music every time I take a turn I've been taking for the past 7 years!!  **See feature request below for how I would deal with this * It can't seem to keep me logged in.  I signed up years ago and logged in, then switched names and screwed something up I guess, because now I can get logged in and see my score, and friends that are driving too and all that cool stuff, but then a week later it loses my info and all my friends and scores disappear.  I add so much content that I should be grand emperor or something, but I've just given up now. * It asks for a review at *exactly* the wrong time, I would have left a review years ago, but waze asks at the beginning of a trio when I'm in a hurry and not at the end when I'm probably about to sit down for a while and fiddle on my phone.  Timing is important   Feature request: * Let me save routes, like coming home from work, or going to work. Assume I take the same route every day and *don't* tell me any of the turns on my route, unless there is a faster way, then only tell me the variations.  Summary: It's useful, but for me it's only stable for short trips, it has some reliability issues that, if fixed, would make it a lot more handy.

Author: Dirk Kessler
Body: Geht so, Umleitung um den Stau funktioniert hier manchmal gut, oft wird der Stau zu spät erkannt. Routenführung war täglich total unlogisch und nicht optimal. Habe Waze echt ein Weile getestet, aber es bringt mich definitiv schlechter als Maps, Here oder Sygic ans Ziel, desweiteren fehlt mir einfach die Übersichtlichkeit der Route, wenn ich fix was suchen muss. Benzinpreise sollten unbedingt über die Marktransparentstelle eingepflegt werden oder ganz weglassen, denn so wie es aktuell gehandhabt wird, bringt es nicht's Ich hab Waze wieder deinstalliert und bin zurück zu Maps, da passt alles besser für mich. Andere werden mit Waze glücklich, so ist's

App: Waze - GPS, Maps, Traffic Alerts & Live Navigation
Author: Clément M
Body: Utilisateur de maps, coyote et Waze. Waze est le meilleur en itinéraires et en guidage (on est quasi sur d'avoir le meilleur itinéraire et de comprendre les instructions. Je n'essaie plus d'être plus malin que lui, il gagne a chaque fois). La base de données des radars fixes et mobiles est maintenant meilleure que celle de coyote (j'ai mes deux allumés en permanence). En comparaison, Coyote a des limitations fausses, des signalement obsolètes et, certes rarement des signalements manquants.  Mais Waze ne sait toujours pas bien avertir dès zones de danger. Il parle trop (entrée dans la zone, sortie de la zone, et en général un votre plusieurs "police signalée.." par radar fixe) mais ne sait toujours pas bipper pour les dépassement de vitesse dans les zones de contrôle, c'est trop facile de se faire flasher par inadvertance (c'est le raison pour laquelle j'ai toujours coyote...) Il est aussi peu performant en recherche d'adresse ou de lieux, parfois il change l'heure d'arrivée 10 fois en 1 trajet (jusqu'à 15 minutes à la fois, surtout à Paris. "Il y a plus de bouchons +15min" "on a un meilleur trajet -8 min") et il s'éteint, se bloque, oubli l'itinéraire (heureusement assez peu, et avec un bon téléphone c'est vite relancé)

Author: Ryan Weddell
Body: Mostly good, navigation routes are a bit odd at times taking you on lots of back roads.  Not very good with Android Auto though on my s7 edge. It crashes often and when I voice search an address it only finds the street not the street number. If I say "102 Some Street" it will only come up with the street name not the number. So if it is a very long street for example this is no good it often takes me to wrong place.  I have to type in the address to navigate to a number which is dangerous when driving and completely illegal in Australia.   If you could fix these issues I would use Waze all the time. Google Maps is much more reliable and useful on Android Auto.

(même en ayant changer de téléphone ) A quand un vraie fonction de GPS qui nous permet de calculer un itinéraire à partir d'un point différent de la ou on se trouve ???? Et à quand des informations de bouchons mis à jours ?? Bouchon a 7h du mat résorbé à 8 mais qui restent jusqu'à 11h!!! Body: Наверное лучший. Всё замечательно. Есть только один баг. В России очень много мест, где нет интернета. Так вот очень часто, после потери соединения , Waze не может подключится снова, хотя интернет уже появился. Приходится выключать Waze, заходить в него снова и снова ставить точки. Translated Body: Probably the best. Everything is great. There is only one bug. There are a lot of places in Russia where there is no Internet. So very often, after losing the connection, Waze can not connect again, although the Internet has already appeared. It is necessary to turn off Waze, to go into it again and again to put points. And on the move it can not be done. I'll be back when Waze learns to reconnect to the server itself.

Plus court certainement mais j'y ai perdu un enjoliveur et portière avant gauche rayée par les ronces dépassant de la végétation luxuriante de l'Aveyron. Impossible de faire demi tour donc il a fallu que je me régale à faire 7 km pour au final rattraper une nationale sur laquelle j'y étais...... Je n'avais pourtant pas programmé le mode paysan. Rectifiez nous ça car visiblement nous sommes nombreux à se plaindre de cette malfonction. Une petite mise à jour ne serait pas du luxe. Ceci dit je ne m'en passe plus. PS: je vous envoi la facture ?😀
Translated Body: Make me go through muddy roads or only a tractor goes regularly I do not understand. Shorter certainly but I lost a hubcap and left front door striped by brambles protruding from the lush vegetation of Aveyron. Impossible to turn back so I had to enjoy 7 km to finally catch a national on which I was ...... I had not yet programmed the peasant mode. Correct us because obviously we are many to complain about this malfunction. A small update would not be luxury. That said, I do not care anymore. PS: I send you the invoice?

Author: Lonnie Marion
Body: This is a follow up to my last review where I rated the app a 2.5.  I have changed the rating to a 1.    I transferred the app to my new phone and although the app recognized my phone number and acknowledged my account, the app would not open with my account.    Therefore, all my favorites as well as my history is lost and unusable.  I used to like Waze because it does a better job of routing around traffic than Google Maps.    I have now switched to Google and only turn Waze on in the rare occasion Google is not showing me a way around the traffic.  I live in California. Otherwise I recommend staying with Google Maps as it is more stable and has never lost my route information. I had used Waze for approximately 6 years.  Nevermore.

Author: Roberto F
Body: Demora para atualizar, as vezes da voltas desnecessárias em um percurso simples,tornando o percurso mais longo e demorado e não é por causa do trânsito.  No mais é satisfatório, mas precisa melhorar bastante! Na navegação em rotas, não dá mais para escolher a mais rápida e a mais curta, tiraram um dos melhores recursos do aplicativo. Se continuar assim piorando, vou deixar de usar o Waze,pois consome muita bateria e banda larga enquanto similares fazem a mesma coisa sem consumir tanto.
Translated Body: It takes time to update, sometimes unnecessary laps on a simple route, making the route longer and time consuming and not because of traffic. No more is satisfactory, but it needs to improve a lot! In route navigation, you can no longer choose the fastest and the shortest, they have taken one of the best features of the application. If it continues to get worse, I will stop using Waze because it consumes a lot of battery and bandwidth while similar ones do the same thing without consuming as much.

Subject: Update
Body: Pls update back Shorter or Faster option

Author: Sallet
Subject: Now a crap app  that’s lost most functionality
Body: I've used Waze for a long time now but the latest changes to reporting hazards has near enough destroyed the functionality of the app. In the UK it is now illegal to interact with the mobile phone by touch while driving. So Waze remove the ability to wave at the phone to bring up the voice commands for a system with 3finger touch. This appears not to work as the background music goes off for about 1 second before returning making it impossible to use voice commands. The response from Waze support? "This is a new innovation!"! My advice is don't upgrade and if you haven't downloaded it as a new user then don't! I have rolled back to an old version which works (4.0.1) and won’t update till the developers are sacked and replaced.

Author: Bex Libby
Subject: Where are my points?
Body: For the past few days the app has not changed my points on my scoreboard. The last time this happened it was updating that update ended up to be a nightmare. I honestly hope that this is not happening right now. You need to stop freezing the points so it can update. This is ridiculous and not to mention dumb when this happens. I also would like to say that it would be nice when it has no limits to the number of times that you can click on it. When you do not drive that much and then you do it would be nice if it was the case. The other thing is that it would be nice if you can click on it when you are walking and you can help the other fellow members in the area out when they are there. I also wish that there was something that helps with the parking lot. One I think that I will remember where I park the car and two it is really annoying when it pops up about a parking spot. The other thing is that if someone drops me off somewhere else I feel like I have to drive the car in the neighborhood just to get it back to where I live. Also to what is wrong with the fact that it needs to have wifi in order for it to work. What is wrong with the slow updates that takes three days to get any points after you have driven?

Author: Kiwanee
Subject: Update to add HOV completely screwed up directions
Body: I’ve been using Waze for a few years now. They did an update about 6 months ago that started recognizing the HOV on my drive to work. It’s like they added it not realizing what it is. They treat it like a toll road which it is absolutely not! In some areas you can pay a toll to drive as a single passenger on a HOV, but not most and certainly not the one on my drive. Also it always thinks I’m on the HOV! Which like traditional HOVs, the one on my route is ONE WAY and changes directions depending on the time of day. I can’t take it HOV toward the city in the afternoon even if I wanted to bc it goes the opposite direction. I have sent dozens of map issues to Waze and either get no response or the most unintelligent response. It’s just not worth it anymore. I’ve also had a lot of issues of it taking me in circles. It tells me to exit and then 2 lights later has me get back on. For no reason! Find another app guys. Almost any app is bound to be better.

Author: Pucho78
Subject: Street names
Body: It would be more helpful if Waze could name the streets where you are supposed to turn into in addition to the number of feet.

Author: Albino1994
Subject: Da rivedere !!!
Body: Sono andato in Spagna e non è uscita la lingua italiana con nomi di strade ecc ma solo spagnola ed altre lingue !!!
Translated Body: I went to Spain and did not leave the Italian language with street names etc. but only Spanish and other languages ​​!!!

Author: 999Responder
Subject: Waze STILL NOT reading reviews.
Body:
Yep, just re apply previous review, as the developers simply DO NOT CARE about what WE WOULD LIKE. For months, I’ve been asking for Lorry profile and what do we get? A bloody motorcycle.

Previous Review Below:

Since my last three reviews, none of my suggestions or comments were even considered. So, A drop down to 1 Star and reiterating again my points and suggestions.

A good SatNav with good routing (for a car/motorbike) with good alerts for cameras, speed etc but not very good if you drive into locations where mobile signal is non-existent. So, how about making the UK map a complete download, so the only time you need to use a mobile network is for traffic and other live alerts so it saves the individuals data plan from becoming used up.

Negatives:

This app is not intended for long duration usage as my iPhone 7 Plus gets extremely hot from using the app, even in non-navigation mode after 30 minutes.

Why am I seeing McDonalds icons on my map? Are they sponsoring you for displaying their logo? If not, I want to be able to delete them and any other companies that I have not selected to be shown.

Why do we need to report if we see Police??? If you cannot drive within the Law, you shouldn't be on the road. I would suggest you remove this alert, as you have an Accident report button. Using the report for seeing Police has the interpretation for individuals to drive illegally and to warn others.

...and finally. Trying to add my workplace to my details and with your map, it is impossible to pin point the address. Type in 1 and it puts you at one end of the street. Type in 3 and it puts you at the other end. WHY CAN’T YOU SIMPLY GO TO MAP, DOUBLE CLICK ON PRECISE LOCATION (to drop your flag/pin), THEN ADD WORKPLACE?????

WHY DO YOU HAVE TO MAKE THINGS IMPOSSIBLE? Yes I’m typing as if I’m shouting (full caps), because you’re simply a useless piece of 💩 that LISTENS TO NO ONE!

Author: EllyMay808
Subject: New Feature
Body: The last update came with a feature I’m sure they won’t advertise but I will be happy to let people know. A pop-up will show on your phone after you update telling you that this app will now be accessing your location even when you aren’t using it to collect data. I assume that means that it’s going to somehow override whatever setting you have it as in your privacy settings. Which means even if you have it set to “while using” or possibly even “never” they may still be accessing your location and collecting data. Just a PSA since their update section didn’t have that feature posted.

Subject: Some bugs I’d like fixed

This is fixed by setting it to avoid tolls, but Waze thinks magic ferries are available anytime and you don’t have to wait in line and you will always get on the first ferry.  Lastly, yesterday for the first time it took me to the wrong address: It took me to the 56th block even though the address destination clearly was in the 96th block.

Author: DZG56
Subject: The interactive aspect makes it awesome
Body: Being able to update and instantly receive other's updates regarding the trip conditions is STELLAR! One thing that I wish for often is for the "sleep/pause" function to be available in the icons that appear when I touch the map screen or even on the bottom row of touchables. Oftentimes I just need or want to stop for something quickly and don't want all the rerouting conversation and map changing stuff going on. Having a sleep button right on top as easy as the reporting functions would be just great! The layering of the maps in color to assist in the dense "mix-masters" of today's big city highways is REALLY helpful. Thanks for this evolved Super GPS++!

Author: Palombaro82
Subject: Perfetta ma…
Body: Applicazione perfetta, completamente gratuita e  con molte funzioni utili. Può essere usata Sia con la connessione Internet attiva, che con la connessione Internet disattivata (In questo caso non avremo informazioni sul traffico). Per via del mio lavoro, (autista corriere), il navigatore è un grande aiuto, fino a poco tempo fa usavo il tomtom, ma da quando scoperto questa applicazione ho smesso di usarlo, poiché trovo waze nettamente migliore. Unica pecca se così possiamo chiamarla, è se imposti una destinazione, puoi aggiungere solo una fermata intermedia. Mentre per via del mio lavoro, avrebbe fatto comodopoter inserire molto più fermate tra il punto di partenza e il punto di arrivo.
Translated Body: Perfect application, completely free and with many useful features. It can be used Whether with the active Internet connection, or with the Internet connection disabled (in this case we will not have traffic information). Because of my work, (driver courier), the browser is a great help, until recently I used the tomtom, but since I discovered this application I stopped using it, because I find waze much better. The only flaw if we can call it, is if you set a destination, you can only add an intermediate stop. While because of my work, it would have made comodopoter insert a lot more stops between the starting point and the point of arrival.

Author: MaybeAfterLunch
Subject: Pro Tips (below 4.31.0.1 review)
Body:
Dec. 1017: Hooray! Liam Newsom actually announces "traffic reported ahead"! Unfortunately OK[ay] Waze not understanding "yes" response to "is that correct?" when reporting. 

2017. 11. 29 i’m loving the new OK Waze feature! On my first drive I was successfully able to OK Waze a destination as well as Report moderate traffic, object on road, and a stopped vehicle (on shoulder). Waze only crashed once in 35 minutes. Hopefully in the future I can OK Waze to “thumb up” and “not there” existing reports. I will update the rest of my review shortly.

2017.11.8 “iOS 4.32 - Fixed some bugs so you can avoid traffic and get to your destination faster with Waze.” Would it be too much to ask for a detailed changelog of fixes in each version? I’ll update my review as I test each feature. +/- zero stars until then. 
_____

    Version 4.31.0.1 has major issues: 
    Not shutting down automatically if you aren't driving: If you forget to tap <search> then <power> at the end of your drive, waze will continue to run, even if you're sitting on the couch with your iPhone locked, draining your battery. 
    Send ETA confirmation says "ETA sent to 0 friends!" (It actually works, the variable in the confirmation is simply not being passed correctly… Hello? Anybody take ITS/CS-101?)
    Second ETA button inexplicably removed… you know, that super usefull one that instantly sends your ETA to your top friend on waze, like your spouse or significant other…? Gone! Probably to many complaints from fat fingered idioys sending their ETA "Bae's crib" to their wives by mistake! Thanks for ruining it for the rest of us, just like the now-disabled report speed limit button in the map controls. (Edit: I can’t figure out why this button is intermittently available. Locations you have both driven to? Inconsistent. Locations you have shared with one another? Inconsistent. Driving to the same location? Inconclusive. 
    I guess it's too complicated for the Waze Coders to put an option in the settings menu, defaulting to Off…
    STILL not announcing "Heavy Traffic reported ahead!" The only voice where this alert was functional was Fuze! with Mr. T, which was removed months ago. People in my area have resorted to reporting Vehicle Stopped on Road to alert other Wazers that the freeway is stop and go. 
    STILL not receiving Time to Leave notifications. Yes, I've checked all my settings after each 'update' since they stopped working and even toggled them off and back on again just in case. 

    Can we please get the microphone button on the main screen as part of the map controls? The new distracted driving law in Oregon levies steep fines to any driver who touches their mounted device more than ONE time to initiate or respond to any app or function any time the vehicle is not legally parked in a marked parking space…

    Minus 2 more stars
_____

    New in recent versions: Landscape mode support and optimization, finally! Request roadside assistance from fellow Wazers in the Report menu! Flat tire? Out of gas? Report roadside assistance needed, type your details in the comments and viola! 

    Now on iOS! Go to <settings> <Voice directions> to record your own navigation sounds, change the ones you don't like, or simply add an audible alert for HEAVY TRAFFIC REPORTED AHEAD. (broken for almost a year on most voices)

    I have recently removed one star, and then another from my rating. If anyone needs this much advice to use their GPS it simply isn't intuitive enough:

    Waze early, Waze often: Launch Waze before you start your vehicle. Always Navigate to your destination, even if you know all the traffic patterns and shortcuts in your sleep. *Only Waze knows about that accident, car fire, flood, or bridge collapse, 15-25 minutes before official reports, in my experience.  

    After you input your destination, Waze presents a primary routing. IMMEDIATELY tap the Routes icon. Next, tap the Map View tab and -> select your preferred route based on distance, ETA, left turns, slums, TOLLS and incidents on the routes. 

    Headed into a crowded metro area? Tap the Add a Stop button on the Waze Dashboard and hit the (P) icon to find ample parking near your destination (and estimated walking time between the two)

    Want to avoid toll roads altogether? Navigation > Avoid Toll Roads

    Never ignore the *Traffic is Pilling-Up Ahead alert. Something unusual is happening, and it will get worse before you get there. Follow the re-route ASAP. (Recently I hopped off I-5 near Seattle and enjoyed a leisurely lunch after a tractor-trailer smashed through the median, reducing both directions to only one lane. The whole region was snarled! #WazeWin)

    Want snappier prompts without street names? Settings > Sound > Voice Language > (anything but Jane) or record your own!

    At the end of your drive, tap the magnifying glass icon (it will be pulsing), then find the power icon ( ' ) and tap it to pause navigation, and stop contributing traffic data. (Unfortunately Waze has been doing strange things recently when powering down at an added stop (like forgetting your final original destination when re-opening Waze)

    Use a hands-free windshield mount to stay legal while optimizing your GPS reception, and positioning your camera to effortlessly snap photos of standstill traffic or major accidents. (Tap the flash icon twice, every time, to disable the 5-second dashboard illuminating flash)

    Tap AND HOLD the zoom icon while swiping up or down to change zoom levels manually, with only one finger. (I think pinch-to-zoom is too complicated to do accurately while operating a motor vehicle. 

Also,
Change <sound and voice> <Voice commands> <Activate> to (3 finger tap) to prevent unwanted interruptions… (wave) and (wave twice) are way too sensitive …

In most versions, tap on the speedometer to report an incorrect or missing speed limit. (May not be currently available)

    -Enthusiastic user, even yet, of Waze since 2012

Author: Auddems
Subject: Overall good, a few things could go better
Body:
Overall, I’m really enjoying this app. I love the fact that anyone can report incidents on the road. I love the score points system. 

Several things could go better. One, I recently requested an edit for a route to a restaurant because the app was trying to get me to go the opposite way of the place. When I sent in the request, I felt the response was rude and a bit abrasive. From “subs5(5)”, I left like I was being talked to like a 5-year-old, and you need to work your communication skills. For example: they didn’t really seem to read my edit request, they pretty much said “if you have a problem, you need to go to ROUTES, you picked the shortest way”. Well duh I picked the shortest way, but it still kept trying to take me the opposite way like toward another town. Second of all, the all-caps is not necessary. 

You plead for users to help edit if we feel it needs it yet get talked down to by certain responders. I also tried to respond to this person’s rude comment, but there was no way to respond back.  Ridiculous

Also, it would be nice if It said the street names and how many miles it will take to get to places besides looking at the app while trying to drive to figure it out. Another issue that’s been going on is it sometimes just shuts down during a route for no reason. If I’m driving long-distances, I don’t want to feel like I have to check it few minutes to make sure it’s still working. 

Overall it was improved!

Author: Cdmcquee
Subject: Love Most of It
Body:
I use Waze a lot, for point-to-point travel for work, for ride-share navigation, and for personal use. I’ve noticed some issues:

1) Sometimes the black bar at the top that shows the next turn will shrink vertically, typically when an ad is displayed. Often after the ad disappears, that black bar will not return to its normal size, and at that point it is no longer possible to tap on it to bring up the list of all upcoming turns.

2) Sometimes the app will crash when the voice is just beginning to recite the next turn. I think this tends to happen during periods of heavy ride-share use in my area, so maybe there is a corelation.

3) Sometimes Waze will direct me to a destination that is often the “back” of where I intend to go. This happens most often in urban environments, typically when streets are laid out in a grid pattern. It also seems to happen more with destinations that are large commercial establishments, such as hotels, apartment buildings, office towers, etc. An example is the Crystal Tea Room at 100 East Penn Square in Philadelphia, PA. The main entrance is on East Penn Square/Juniper, but Waze has twice directed me to the back, on South 13th Street.

Author: NovaTerrian
Subject: Great app but has a few major flaws!
Body:
Like this app a lot, but there’s a few things that really damage the rating for me:
Major one: font color and size. I am twenty and only have mild vision problems, but I still need to lean forward to view a lot of instructions from about four feet away. Being able to change font size is INCREDIBLY IMPORTANT for accessibility. The blue on black is cool looking, but can make reading difficult. For this app to function for navigation I need to be able to actually read instructions. 
Minor one(s): it’s a little slow to realize you missed a turn or something, and often times can differentiate frontage road from highway. Sometimes it “freezes” with the loading circle of doom endlessly spinning. Easy enough to fix with an app restart while not driving, harder while driving.

Subject: Hate new update!
Body: When they updated the app, all I got when I opened it was a black screen. I finally had to delete and reinstall the app. So of course, I lost ALL of my saved information. I couldn’t seem to log in to retrieve it, so I had to start ALL over again. The other issue I am having is, although I have my Location in settings set to “while using the app”, Waze continues to use my location, unless I turn it off. Leaving it on drains the battery, so I have to turn it off, and then back on EVERY time I want to use the app!! What a hassle!!! I love the app, when I an using it; it is great! I just really HATE the new update!

Author: Theland48
Subject: Versione 4.34 - Buona ma......
Body: Buona App perché abbastanza affidabile e gratuita. Finalmente con questo ultimo aggiornamento è possibile usare l'App con la localizzazione solo quando in uso. Prima erano solo due possibilità: o sempre acceso o sempre spento. Era ora che facessero questa funzione per non scaricare la batteria quando non in uso. Purtroppo NON è proprio così!!!!!! Provate a settare: "Solo quando in uso" e poi chiudete Waze e vedrete in alto la scritta "Waze sta usando la tua posizione" che stacca il GPS dopo molto ma molto tempo e NON SEMPRE. Almeno così succede sul mio 7plus con IOS 10.3.3. Spero se ne accorgano e che risolvino presto riducendo il tempo di connessione al GPS dopo aver chiuso l'applicazione. Mancano, inoltre, ancora alcune strade secondarie ma i continui aggiornamenti fan ben sperare. Comunque cosa non particolarmente importante percorrendo le strade principali. È già passabile cosi anche se io la uso solo per vedere il traffico e relativi intoppi alla circolazione. Inoltre è gratuita!
Translated Body: Good App because quite reliable and free. Finally with this last update it is possible to use the App with the localization only when in use. Before there were only two possibilities: either always on or always off. It was time that they did this to not drain the battery when not in use. Unfortunately it is not so !!!!!! Try setting: "Only when in use" and then close Waze and you will see at the top the words "Waze is using your position" which disconnects the GPS after a very long time and NOT ALWAYS. At least that's what happens on my 7plus with IOS 10.3.3. I hope they notice it and solve it soon reducing the connection time to the GPS after closing the application. Furthermore, there are still some secondary roads, but the continuous updates hope well. However, this is not particularly important when traveling along the main roads. It is already passable so even if I use it only to see the traffic and related traffic hitches. It is also free!

Author: hayley.48
Subject: Sometimes helps but not enough info
Body: The way that this app diverts the route to avoid impending traffic causes more trouble than it’s worth. Getting off major roads to favor dangerous and winding streets can add stress and unwanted complexity to a trip. It would be helpful if waze would give the navigator and option before changing the route. This app has introduced hard situations including ending up driving through very unsafe parts of cities and having to deal with mountainous backroads on a snowy day. The developer should consider adjusting the counter routes waze encourages.

Author: Tantan25
Subject: Bummer

Author: Loving it still!!!!!

Body:
Don’t update!! Latest update is the worst! No longer reroutes to better routes after traffic delay updates. I had to manually click on route options to see what better routes were available. 
No longer have navigation option for shorter or faster routes. 
The GUI now has a big box obstructing the map. 
It’s only useful now for road condition updates by users. SMH

Author: Bruno Boque
Subject: Waze espelhando no AppRadio
Body:
Waze, nesta última versão 4.34 voltou a espelhar o app nas centrais multimídia Pioneer através do AppRadio, porém
 Esta travando constantemente no espelhamento e poucos botões funcionam no espelhamento.... é necessário fazer alguns ajustes fino para corrigir estes problemas...
Translated Body: Waze, in this latest version 4.34 came back to mirror the app in Pioneer multimedia hubs through AppRadio, however It is constantly locking in mirroring and few buttons work in mirroring .... it is necessary to make some fine adjustments to fix these problems ...

Author: RDavis1792
Subject: Big, fat let down
Body: I’ve heard several people swear by Waze. I downloaded it trying to navigate around closed roads to get to an event. It did get me to my destination, despite numerous closed roads, so I decided to continue using it. On my way home, I passed the final exit for 10 miles and as soon as I did, all I could see was a sea of red break lights. There was a multiple car major crash and there was no warning whatsoever. Thanks, but I’ll stick to my car navigation. It’s never let me down the way Waze has.

Author: Doug.Summers
Subject: Keeps freezing up!
Body: I’ve always loved waze and use it all the time but as of late I’ve noticed that it keeps freezing up on my iPhone 7Plus.  Don’t know if it’s the app or due to Apple slowing phones down. Today it happened 4 times after putting in the location and freezes up for about 10 seconds and shuts down, even after restarting my phone.

Author: avesoriano
Subject: Worse update.
Body: Im stuck in the black screen disconnect when i connect it to my cars’s hdmi. Sound is working but i cant see the map anymore. I prefer the older version. Regret updating

Author: cat 85
Subject: Bugs
Body: Waze s’éteint au bout de 2 minutes sur iPhone X.....
Translated Body: Waze turns off after 2 minutes on iPhone X .....

Author: jeffersonblz
Subject: Ótimo App
Body: O Waze é um ótimo aplicativo sem dúvidas nenhumas, mas tem seus pontos que precisam ser revistos, os alertas de buraco em vias deveriam ficar por muito mais tempo em exibição, porque no Brasil os buracos não são resolvidos de um dia pro outro, e os alertas saem muito rápido, deveria ficar até que outro Waze informar que o problema com o buraco foi resolvido.
Translated Body: Waze is a great application with no doubts, but it has its points that need to be revised, the hole-in-the-hole alerts should be much longer on display, because in Brazil the holes are not solved overnight, and the warnings come out very fast, it should stay until another Waze reports that the problem with the hole has been solved.

Author: Biazinha32456

Author: Agassi91

Body:
It would be better if it tells you which lane instead of left or right. As hong kong road specific lane will lead you to different highway. A more specific lane alert will be a big pros. 

It will be great if you can choose another color for the upcoming alert. As I'm mainly a night driver the light blue title alert, it's really hard to see when at night time.

Author: Al Khawarizmi
Subject: 😱 Waze régresse 😱 😱 😱 !
Body:
Inadmissible de conserver si longtemps les erreurs d’orthographe grossières signalées par les usagers  bienveillants ... surtout quand on se veut « collaboratif ».
« Une erreur ne devient une faute que si l’on refuse de la corriger ». JFK.
Waze doit grandir !!! 🤓

Author: Fonse_AlineP
Subject: O que está acontecendo?
Body:
Após a ultima atualização o App não encontra sinal GPS (já testei com o 4G e Wi-Fi), demora para encontrar a posição no mapa e está com delay na atualização conforme você avança pelo percurso. Acaba por prejudicar o tempo estimado e errar o caminho. 
Hey, galera do Waze, ajuda a gente!

Author: hermanthefrog
Subject: Wazing Hazing
Body: Guys newest update crashes every time I open the app. I can't even use it anymore unless I sign out of my account and use it as a guest. Real real annoying since I use Waze everyday and would rather not have to go back to using google maps. Please please fix this. It's not me, it's you.

Author: LividLivs
Subject: Untouchable!
Body: There is nothing like this out on the market! This app is soooo user friendly, smart and informative, and really fun actually because I love earning rewards and leveling up. I love being able to beep at my friends driving on the road too. I never take the time to write a review but I am so obsessed with Waze! I open it even when I don’t need navigation and know where I’m going! The traffic and incident awareness and the alternate routes it gives are life saving. Just yesterday I avoided a 53 min traffic jam on the highway, and got to my destination in less than 30 mins, all thanks to Waze! 😍
